<div class="xar-mod-head">
    <span class="xar-mod-title">
        <xar:mlstring>MetaWeblog API Administration</xar:mlstring>
    </span>
</div>

<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
    <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
            <img src="modules/base/xarimages/admin_generic.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
        </div>
             
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
            
            <p>
                <xar:mlstring>The MetaWeblog API is a XML-RPC API used for blogging. 
                It is basically an extended version of the original blogger API, 
                where the format of the messages which can be passed between a client
                and a server is more structured and more rich. Additional support 
                for categorizing posts and integrating other media (like pictures)
                makes this API more attractive for blogging.</xar:mlstring>
            </p>
            <p> 
                This module depends on the availability of the blogger API module, because it reuses the implementation of the
                methods in that API where possible. See that module for more info.
            </p>
        
            <p>
            <xar:mlstring>You can find the specification of the MetaWebloag API at </xar:mlstring>
            <a href="http://http//www.xmlrpc.com/metaWeblogApi">http://http//www.xmlrpc.com/metaWeblogApi</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
